<DOC><DOCNO> AP880430-0165 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-30-88 0038EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-People-Sawyer-Nichols     04-30 0105</FIRST><SECOND>AM-People-Sawyer-Nichols,0107</SECOND><HEAD>Diane Sawyer, Mike Nichols Are Married</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Director Mike Nichols and ``60 Minutes''correspondent Diane Sawyer were married Friday in an afternoonceremony, a CBS News spokesman said.   The couple, who decided to wed after a six-month romance, askedthat the location of the wedding be kept a secret until Saturday,said Roy Brunett.   It was the first marriage for Sawyer, 42, a former aide toPresident Richard M. Nixon, and the third for Nichols, 56, theformer comedian who directed the films ``The Graduate,'' ``CarnalKnowledge'' and ``Silkwood'' and the plays ``The Odd Couple'' and``The Real Thing.''</TEXT></DOC>